1
00:00:20,700 --> 00:00:30,700
[English subtitles are available]

2
00:01:52,320 --> 00:01:55,670
[Moonlight]

3
00:01:55,840 --> 00:01:58,700
[Episode 23]

4
00:01:58,920 --> 00:02:06,270
[Yuan Yue Publishing House]

5
00:02:04,560 --> 00:02:05,929
Xiao Niao.

6
00:02:07,450 --> 00:02:09,250
You're taking all the drafts home?

7
00:02:09,730 --> 00:02:11,600
You're still here?

8
00:02:11,810 --> 00:02:13,130
It is Valentine's Day.

9
00:02:13,130 --> 00:02:15,250
I'm going out with my boyfriend.

10
00:02:15,489 --> 00:02:17,489
Today is Valentine's Day?

11
00:02:17,489 --> 00:02:18,200
Yeah.

12
00:02:18,810 --> 00:02:20,050
It's okay, Chu Li.

13
00:02:20,280 --> 00:02:21,330
You can celebrate too

14
00:02:21,330 --> 00:02:22,730
when you have a boyfriend.

15
00:02:27,250 --> 00:02:28,370
Yes, dear?

16
00:02:30,810 --> 00:02:32,490
You need to work overtime?

17
00:02:32,930 --> 00:02:34,250
Carry on with your work then.

18
00:02:42,890 --> 00:02:44,050
You're still here?

19
00:02:44,970 --> 00:02:45,930
Mr Zhou Chuan.

20
00:02:46,090 --> 00:02:47,170
You just got off work too?

21
00:02:49,170 --> 00:02:50,690
Where are you going?

22
00:02:50,690 --> 00:02:52,050
Can you give me a ride?

23
00:02:52,050 --> 00:02:53,690
We're heading to different directions.

24
00:02:54,370 --> 00:02:56,210
You sure are hilarious.

25
00:02:56,210 --> 00:02:57,800
I haven't said where I'm going.

26
00:02:57,800 --> 00:02:59,450
I know I'm hilarious.

27
00:02:59,650 --> 00:03:00,730
Get in already.

28
00:03:00,730 --> 00:03:01,730
I knew you were joking.

29
00:03:01,730 --> 00:03:04,050
I never said you can get in.

30
00:03:04,640 --> 00:03:06,010
Are you coming or not?

31
00:03:07,279 --> 00:03:09,330
Sure.

32
00:03:09,970 --> 00:03:11,240
Thanks, Mr Zhou Chuan.

33
00:03:11,240 --> 00:03:12,529
The back seat? Really?

34
00:03:12,529 --> 00:03:14,290
Do you think I'm your driver?

35
00:03:16,770 --> 00:03:19,050
We happen to head to the
same direction when going home.

36
00:03:19,050 --> 00:03:20,290
That's why

37
00:03:20,570 --> 00:03:21,970
he will

38
00:03:22,290 --> 00:03:24,090
give me a ride.

39
00:03:24,530 --> 00:03:25,610
Are you done?

40
00:03:25,730 --> 00:03:26,890
Time is flying.

41
00:03:26,960 --> 00:03:27,890
Okay.

42
00:03:32,130 --> 00:03:33,970
Bye, Xiao Niao.

43
00:03:34,330 --> 00:03:35,370
Well,

44
00:03:35,370 --> 00:03:38,010
it's fine to have Chu Li sit beside me.

45
00:03:38,010 --> 00:03:40,170
My girlfriend likes her as an editor.

46
00:03:41,410 --> 00:03:42,330
Bye.

47
00:03:51,910 --> 00:03:53,630
[Yun Fei]

48
00:04:01,050 --> 00:04:01,930
Bai Zhi.

49
00:04:02,610 --> 00:04:03,890
Regarding the fans

50
00:04:04,160 --> 00:04:06,010
the other day,

51
00:04:06,290 --> 00:04:07,650
I'm really sorry.

52
00:04:07,800 --> 00:04:10,130
It's my bad for being careless
when it comes to publication.

53
00:04:10,130 --> 00:04:11,170
It's not your problem.

54
00:04:11,490 --> 00:04:12,200
We finally get to

55
00:04:12,200 --> 00:04:13,890
work with Director Lu Fang.

56
00:04:14,050 --> 00:04:15,529
Cherish it.

57
00:04:15,930 --> 00:04:17,330
But don't rush it too.

58
00:04:19,730 --> 00:04:21,250
Today is Valentine's Day.

59
00:04:21,370 --> 00:04:22,650
What's your plan?

60
00:04:23,050 --> 00:04:24,770
Finishing my work.

61
00:04:24,930 --> 00:04:26,850
You should go home too.
Do what you need to do.

62
00:04:33,610 --> 00:04:34,610
Okay.

63
00:04:48,450 --> 00:04:49,720
Why are you smiling?

64
00:04:51,090 --> 00:04:54,770
Don't you find it romantic?
Rain on the Valentine's Day.

65
00:04:55,170 --> 00:04:56,970
Didn't you listen to the weather forecast?

66
00:04:56,970 --> 00:04:58,850
It's supposed to rain at this hour.

67
00:04:59,170 --> 00:05:00,210
It will stop later.

68
00:05:00,210 --> 00:05:01,370
Besides,

69
00:05:01,370 --> 00:05:02,090
I don't care

70
00:05:02,090 --> 00:05:04,170
about a festival
that only favours the capitalists.

71
00:05:05,890 --> 00:05:07,530
But this is

72
00:05:07,530 --> 00:05:09,170
our first Valentine's Day.

73
00:05:09,170 --> 00:05:11,530
Yes, the first Valentine's Day.

74
00:05:11,530 --> 00:05:13,770
And Jiang Yu Cheng
asked you out for dinner.

75
00:05:13,770 --> 00:05:15,290
He must have an evil intention.

76
00:05:15,930 --> 00:05:17,690
What did you say?

77
00:05:17,690 --> 00:05:19,690
He asked you out too, didn't he?

78
00:05:22,570 --> 00:05:23,770
What is it?

79
00:05:23,770 --> 00:05:25,970
Are you in a bad mood?

80
00:05:25,970 --> 00:05:27,570
And why did you bring up

81
00:05:27,570 --> 00:05:29,970
the girlfriend topic
all of a sudden just now?

82
00:05:32,690 --> 00:05:35,040
Forget it. Never mind.

83
00:05:35,600 --> 00:05:37,730
By the way, I talked to Yu Yao today.

84
00:05:37,730 --> 00:05:39,210
I'm almost done with my research.

85
00:05:39,210 --> 00:05:41,890
Starting tomorrow,
I won't be working at Yuan Yue anymore.

86
00:05:51,050 --> 00:05:52,490
Mr Zhou.

87
00:05:52,760 --> 00:05:54,170
Are you really not going to

88
00:05:54,170 --> 00:05:56,170
do anything on Valentine's Day?

89
00:05:56,810 --> 00:05:59,090
Tell me what you want. I'll buy it.

90
00:06:01,170 --> 00:06:02,330
Forget it.

91
00:06:08,410 --> 00:06:10,330
Cheers.

92
00:06:11,210 --> 00:06:13,170
Don't drink too much wine.

93
00:06:14,490 --> 00:06:17,330
I haven't even started.

94
00:06:19,450 --> 00:06:20,210
Chu Li.

95
00:06:20,370 --> 00:06:22,210
I have to thank you this time.

96
00:06:22,800 --> 00:06:25,210
I heard that you fell sick
and hurt your back

97
00:06:25,210 --> 00:06:26,440
because of me.

98
00:06:26,650 --> 00:06:28,130
My apologies.

99
00:06:28,130 --> 00:06:31,010
Please don't mind
about the contract termination.

100
00:06:31,370 --> 00:06:33,920
It's okay. It's my honour to help you

101
00:06:33,920 --> 00:06:37,000
get your book published.
All my efforts are worth it.

102
00:06:39,330 --> 00:06:41,610
Hi. Today is Valentine's Day.

103
00:06:41,610 --> 00:06:43,160
We are holding an event.

104
00:06:43,160 --> 00:06:45,650
If a man confesses to the lady he likes,

105
00:06:45,650 --> 00:06:47,370
they will be given a bouquet of flower.

106
00:06:47,370 --> 00:06:48,810
Do you need it?

107
00:06:49,530 --> 00:06:50,610
Ask him.

108
00:06:51,330 --> 00:06:52,010
Me?

109
00:06:54,720 --> 00:06:56,970
Never mind.
I don't celebrate Valentine's Day.

110
00:06:57,970 --> 00:06:59,290
Sorry for disturbing.

111
00:06:59,290 --> 00:07:01,200
Enjoy your meal.

112
00:07:04,609 --> 00:07:06,650
I'll answer the call outside.

113
00:07:09,410 --> 00:07:10,530
Don't tell me

114
00:07:10,530 --> 00:07:12,320
you prepared nothing for Valentine's Day.

115
00:07:12,320 --> 00:07:14,770
Do I need to tell you?

116
00:07:15,170 --> 00:07:16,370
No.

117
00:07:16,370 --> 00:07:18,010
But you need to let Chu Li know.

118
00:07:18,010 --> 00:07:19,210
This is your

119
00:07:19,210 --> 00:07:20,770
first Valentine's Day, after all.

120
00:07:20,770 --> 00:07:22,650
You're acting like you don't care at all.

121
00:07:22,650 --> 00:07:24,370
I want to let her feel disappointed

122
00:07:24,370 --> 00:07:27,090
before showing my surprising gift.

123
00:07:27,400 --> 00:07:29,690
You know nothing
for someone who had a girlfriend.

124
00:07:30,610 --> 00:07:31,850
Fine.

125
00:07:32,090 --> 00:07:33,810
You're getting tricky.

126
00:07:38,400 --> 00:07:39,720
Hello, Chief Editor Yu.

127
00:07:39,720 --> 00:07:41,210
The Disappearing Amusement Park

128
00:07:41,210 --> 00:07:42,930
is of high importance to the higher-ups.

129
00:07:42,930 --> 00:07:45,290
They increased the marketing fee

130
00:07:45,290 --> 00:07:47,330
and have promised to publish it

131
00:07:47,330 --> 00:07:48,850
in one month.

132
00:07:49,650 --> 00:07:51,650
Is that true? Awesome.

133
00:07:51,650 --> 00:07:53,690
I'm having dinner with Mr Jiang.

134
00:07:53,690 --> 00:07:55,410
I'll tell him now.

135
00:07:55,410 --> 00:07:57,370
You're having dinner with him?

136
00:07:57,370 --> 00:07:58,970
Isn't it Valentine's Day?

137
00:08:00,010 --> 00:08:01,010
You two...

138
00:08:01,010 --> 00:08:02,450
Nothing like that.

139
00:08:02,450 --> 00:08:04,890
Mr Jiang wanted to buy me a meal

140
00:08:04,890 --> 00:08:06,130
to thank me. That's all.

141
00:08:06,130 --> 00:08:07,890
Mr Zhou Chuan is here too.

142
00:08:08,410 --> 00:08:10,080
Calm down.

143
00:08:10,290 --> 00:08:11,490
Many writers and editors

144
00:08:11,490 --> 00:08:13,330
fell in love too in the past.

145
00:08:13,330 --> 00:08:15,090
[If you're together,]

146
00:08:15,090 --> 00:08:16,800
I will give you my sincere blessing.

147
00:08:17,770 --> 00:08:19,650
But doesn't Mr Zhou Chuan

148
00:08:19,650 --> 00:08:21,410
have a girlfriend? If I'm not mistaken.

149
00:08:22,770 --> 00:08:24,130
I think so.

150
00:08:24,450 --> 00:08:25,810
He's eating with you guys

151
00:08:25,810 --> 00:08:27,450
[instead of being with his girlfriend?]

152
00:08:27,610 --> 00:08:29,370
[What a funny guy.]

153
00:08:29,610 --> 00:08:30,970
So, enjoy your dinner.

154
00:08:30,970 --> 00:08:32,250
I'm just calling to let you know.

155
00:08:32,970 --> 00:08:35,010
Okay. Bye.

156
00:08:44,410 --> 00:08:45,490
Mr Jiang.

157
00:08:45,490 --> 00:08:47,050
I have a good news for you.

158
00:08:47,050 --> 00:08:49,130
Chief Editor Yu said
the higher-ups think really highly

159
00:08:49,130 --> 00:08:50,730
of The Disappearing Amusement Park

160
00:08:50,730 --> 00:08:52,999
that they added
a huge sum of marketing fee,

161
00:08:52,999 --> 00:08:54,129
and promised to

162
00:08:54,129 --> 00:08:56,170
publish the book in a month.

163
00:08:57,050 --> 00:09:00,090
That means it won't clash

164
00:09:00,090 --> 00:09:01,690
with Huang Quan Inn's publication.

165
00:09:03,249 --> 00:09:04,290
Too bad.

166
00:09:04,450 --> 00:09:06,410
I thought of competing with you.

167
00:09:07,410 --> 00:09:08,610
Chief Editor Yu also asked

168
00:09:08,610 --> 00:09:09,930
if you want

169
00:09:09,930 --> 00:09:12,130
a signing event on the launching day.

170
00:09:13,210 --> 00:09:14,570
Signing event?

171
00:09:16,170 --> 00:09:17,010
Okay.

172
00:09:17,010 --> 00:09:19,050
When the speech on the film was cancelled,

173
00:09:19,050 --> 00:09:21,160
it was a pity for many
fans who were at the event.

174
00:09:22,010 --> 00:09:23,170
Thank you, Mr Jiang.

175
00:09:23,170 --> 00:09:26,370
I will see to it that
your book is published.

176
00:09:30,450 --> 00:09:32,090
Can we not talk about work

177
00:09:32,090 --> 00:09:34,010
and just enjoy our meal?

178
00:09:37,170 --> 00:09:38,810
By the way, Chu Li,

179
00:09:38,810 --> 00:09:41,200
I heard you went to see Director Lu Fang

180
00:09:41,200 --> 00:09:42,290
on the aeroplane.

181
00:09:42,290 --> 00:09:43,610
You even talked through the entire flight.

182
00:09:44,250 --> 00:09:46,040
It was so close.

183
00:09:46,040 --> 00:09:47,570
When I got to Linzhou,

184
00:09:47,570 --> 00:09:49,090
he already passed the custom.

185
00:09:49,090 --> 00:09:50,930
Fortunately, I booked a ticket

186
00:09:50,930 --> 00:09:52,810
of the same flight in advance.

187
00:09:52,810 --> 00:09:55,160
That's how we stopped him on the plane.

188
00:09:57,850 --> 00:09:59,170
"We"?

189
00:10:01,170 --> 00:10:04,330
Me. Alone.

190
00:10:04,810 --> 00:10:07,010
Luckily, it was a domestic flight.

191
00:10:07,010 --> 00:10:08,410
I couldn't have done anything

192
00:10:08,410 --> 00:10:10,210
if he was going abroad.

193
00:10:13,810 --> 00:10:14,930
Chu Li.

194
00:10:15,930 --> 00:10:17,690
Does Gu Bai Zhi have anything to do

195
00:10:18,410 --> 00:10:20,250
with my cooperation with Director Lu?

196
00:10:21,850 --> 00:10:23,930
Why did you ask that?

197
00:10:25,890 --> 00:10:27,010
Just tell me.

198
00:10:27,010 --> 00:10:28,650
Yes or no.

199
00:10:31,010 --> 00:10:32,290
Yes.

200
00:10:36,010 --> 00:10:37,970
Like what you thought.

201
00:10:38,960 --> 00:10:40,570
The only person who can solve this

202
00:10:40,570 --> 00:10:42,250
or would think of this idea,

203
00:10:42,610 --> 00:10:43,800
and realise it

204
00:10:43,800 --> 00:10:46,650
is Director Gu.

205
00:10:47,810 --> 00:10:49,490
I heard from Mr Zhou Chuan

206
00:10:49,490 --> 00:10:50,890
that tried to have Mr Jiang

207
00:10:50,890 --> 00:10:52,530
collaborate with Director Li Yu,

208
00:10:52,530 --> 00:10:54,040
but it failed.

209
00:10:54,210 --> 00:10:56,530
The only director
who is as famous as him

210
00:10:56,530 --> 00:10:58,440
in the country is Director Lu Fang.

211
00:10:58,930 --> 00:11:00,970
So, is it possible

212
00:11:00,970 --> 00:11:02,770
to help me contact him?

213
00:11:02,770 --> 00:11:05,290
If The Disappearing Amusement Park
can be made into film,

214
00:11:05,290 --> 00:11:07,810
the book can definitely be published.

215
00:11:08,050 --> 00:11:09,530
Why should I help you?

216
00:11:09,880 --> 00:11:11,770
We can persuade Director Lu Fang

217
00:11:11,770 --> 00:11:13,090
to make a series of the film.

218
00:11:13,090 --> 00:11:14,850
By then, you can also sell

219
00:11:14,850 --> 00:11:16,450
the copyright of Yun Fei's work.

220
00:11:16,450 --> 00:11:18,610
These two writers have similar style.

221
00:11:18,610 --> 00:11:21,290
Yun Fei's can somehow
get some popularity back.

222
00:11:22,410 --> 00:11:24,370
I thought you'd play the emotion card

223
00:11:24,370 --> 00:11:26,370
and say Jiang Yu Cheng missed the speech

224
00:11:26,370 --> 00:11:28,130
because of me.

225
00:11:28,970 --> 00:11:30,680
That's the truth, isn't it?

226
00:11:30,770 --> 00:11:32,690
But I'm sure

227
00:11:32,690 --> 00:11:34,330
that even if I don't bring it up,

228
00:11:34,330 --> 00:11:36,490
you'd still try to help him.

229
00:11:36,490 --> 00:11:37,930
You could've just left it to me.

230
00:11:37,930 --> 00:11:39,170
No way.

231
00:11:39,170 --> 00:11:40,450
I'm in charge of him.

232
00:11:40,450 --> 00:11:42,770
I will spare no effort to help him.

233
00:11:42,930 --> 00:11:45,690
And I don't know about you.

234
00:11:45,690 --> 00:11:46,960
So I must

235
00:11:46,960 --> 00:11:48,570
get things under my control.

236
00:11:51,170 --> 00:11:52,650
Let's work together.

237
00:11:52,890 --> 00:11:53,730
Really?

238
00:11:53,730 --> 00:11:55,090
But on one condition.

239
00:11:55,880 --> 00:11:57,290
What's that?

240
00:11:58,170 --> 00:11:59,650
Don't tell Jiang Yu Cheng.

241
00:12:03,010 --> 00:12:05,290
Not only did Director Gu help me,

242
00:12:05,290 --> 00:12:08,130
she even found out
about Director Lu Fang's schedule,

243
00:12:08,130 --> 00:12:10,170
and quickly drove me to Linzhou.

244
00:12:10,490 --> 00:12:11,600
When the tire blew out,

245
00:12:11,600 --> 00:12:14,050
she fixed it on the road.

246
00:12:14,050 --> 00:12:15,610
Her only condition

247
00:12:15,610 --> 00:12:17,690
is not to let you know about it.

248
00:12:23,010 --> 00:12:25,210
It suddenly occurred to me
that I have something on.

249
00:12:25,480 --> 00:12:26,570
You guys enjoy.

250
00:12:44,930 --> 00:12:47,090
Look at you. You must've caught a cold.

251
00:12:48,290 --> 00:12:49,890
Drink warm water
the first thing you get home.

252
00:12:50,610 --> 00:12:53,690
[Drink warm water?
An insensitive man, indeed.]

253
00:12:58,370 --> 00:13:00,330
Put my interest first next time.

254
00:13:00,330 --> 00:13:02,120
Stop working so hard for Jiang Yu Cheng.

255
00:13:02,530 --> 00:13:04,290
I'm in charge of him.

256
00:13:04,290 --> 00:13:06,930
Who else would fight for him if not me?

257
00:13:11,090 --> 00:13:12,010
By the way,

258
00:13:12,010 --> 00:13:14,730
did Gu Bai Zhi say something
I can't listen to the other day?

259
00:13:14,930 --> 00:13:16,970
As she refused to let me enter.

260
00:13:18,490 --> 00:13:21,800
She only gave me a reminder.

261
00:13:21,920 --> 00:13:23,240
I'll get going.

262
00:13:24,120 --> 00:13:25,970
The relationship
between an editor and a writer

263
00:13:25,970 --> 00:13:27,640
isn't really romantic.

264
00:13:28,170 --> 00:13:30,370
It will be harder for you

265
00:13:31,210 --> 00:13:32,650
when the guy is Zhou Chuan.

266
00:13:33,450 --> 00:13:35,090
"It will be harder when the guy

267
00:13:35,090 --> 00:13:35,970
is Zhou Chuan?"

268
00:13:35,970 --> 00:13:37,170
What did she mean?

269
00:13:37,170 --> 00:13:38,530
Is it because she and Jiang Yu Cheng

270
00:13:38,530 --> 00:13:39,810
didn't end well

271
00:13:39,810 --> 00:13:41,210
that she tried to poison your mind?

272
00:13:41,610 --> 00:13:43,040
She's just jealous.

273
00:13:43,600 --> 00:13:45,240
Don't discuss her
experience in the future.

274
00:13:45,490 --> 00:13:47,890
Mr Zhou, I think you should

275
00:13:47,890 --> 00:13:49,850
reflect on yourself instead.

276
00:13:50,730 --> 00:13:51,810
Look.

277
00:13:52,050 --> 00:13:53,410
You don't even bother

278
00:13:53,410 --> 00:13:55,450
to prepare anything on Valentine's Day.

279
00:13:55,450 --> 00:13:57,680
I think Director Gu is right.

280
00:13:57,680 --> 00:13:58,970
Even an outsider

281
00:13:58,970 --> 00:14:00,130
can easily get between us,

282
00:14:00,130 --> 00:14:00,850
is it?

283
00:14:02,650 --> 00:14:04,400
Do you like me or not?

284
00:14:04,840 --> 00:14:06,480
It's a secret.

285
00:14:06,650 --> 00:14:08,570
Say again?

286
00:14:09,810 --> 00:14:11,690
[What do you think?]

287
00:14:11,690 --> 00:14:14,010
[Of course I do.]

288
00:14:17,400 --> 00:14:19,600
[Jiang Yu Cheng]

289
00:14:24,730 --> 00:14:25,890
Hello.

290
00:14:27,490 --> 00:14:28,810
Now?

291
00:14:29,290 --> 00:14:30,800
I'll be right there.

292
00:14:59,840 --> 00:15:02,010
How is your wound? Better?

293
00:15:03,290 --> 00:15:04,770
It has recovered long ago.

294
00:15:07,330 --> 00:15:10,130
I heard from Chu Li that you
even know how to change tyre.

295
00:15:10,130 --> 00:15:12,050
When did you learn that?

296
00:15:12,690 --> 00:15:14,210
So you've learned that.

297
00:15:16,970 --> 00:15:17,970
Thank you.

298
00:15:19,210 --> 00:15:20,690
Well, you didn't even hesitate

299
00:15:20,690 --> 00:15:23,450
to come and help me
once Yun Fei called you.

300
00:15:28,680 --> 00:15:30,250
Jiang Yu Cheng.

301
00:15:31,320 --> 00:15:34,610
Whatever happened,

302
00:15:37,040 --> 00:15:38,610
we once matter a great deal

303
00:15:38,610 --> 00:15:41,050
in each other's lives.

304
00:15:42,760 --> 00:15:44,690
Let's not say thank you.

305
00:15:49,000 --> 00:15:56,800
♫ I've been giddy from drifting
in a sea of people ♫

306
00:15:57,160 --> 00:16:04,880
♫ Unwilling to admit my anticipation
of getting submitted to gentleness ♫

307
00:15:57,810 --> 00:15:58,690
Sir.

308
00:15:58,690 --> 00:16:00,690
Would you like to buy her a rose?

309
00:16:00,690 --> 00:16:01,800
Never mind, girl.

310
00:16:01,800 --> 00:16:03,560
It's okay. How much is it?

311
00:16:03,560 --> 00:16:05,890
-Twenty yuan.
-Okay.

312
00:16:04,880 --> 00:16:12,120
♫ I want to be led by you,
albeit a meager freedom ♫

313
00:16:08,050 --> 00:16:09,010
Here you go.

314
00:16:10,160 --> 00:16:11,890
Thank you.

315
00:16:12,120 --> 00:16:19,030
♫ The Hand of the Creator
has finally heard the call for help ♫

316
00:16:14,560 --> 00:16:16,250
I remember

317
00:16:16,250 --> 00:16:18,370
our first Valentine's Day.

318
00:16:18,370 --> 00:16:20,650
We were silly back then.

319
00:16:19,030 --> 00:16:26,980
♫ I'm drifting in a sea of people.
And will frequently look back ♫

320
00:16:21,210 --> 00:16:23,210
All I care about was working
with books in the bookstore,

321
00:16:23,210 --> 00:16:25,610
and prepared nothing.

322
00:16:26,610 --> 00:16:28,210
I promised

323
00:16:27,100 --> 00:16:34,780
♫ Scared to reach out my hand
that no one will save me ♫

324
00:16:28,450 --> 00:16:30,290
to buy you a rose.

325
00:16:30,810 --> 00:16:32,450
And here it is.

326
00:16:34,780 --> 00:16:42,010
♫ How rich can concrete skyscrapers be ♫

327
00:16:36,050 --> 00:16:37,530
Actually, I didn't really care

328
00:16:37,530 --> 00:16:38,330
about receiving roses

329
00:16:38,330 --> 00:16:40,850
or celebrating Valentine's Day back then.

330
00:16:41,890 --> 00:16:43,600
But, thanks.

331
00:16:42,160 --> 00:16:46,280
♫ You are a rare shining oasis ♫

332
00:16:44,650 --> 00:16:46,130
Didn't you just say

333
00:16:46,130 --> 00:16:49,130
not to say thank you to each other.

334
00:16:46,440 --> 00:16:59,130
♫ Exactly what I want ♫

335
00:17:22,090 --> 00:17:23,290
Go back to your room now.

336
00:17:23,290 --> 00:17:24,930
Don't infect me with it.

337
00:17:25,490 --> 00:17:27,569
I need to burn the midnight oil
to do word coding.

338
00:17:27,930 --> 00:17:29,250
If the instalment is affected,

339
00:17:29,250 --> 00:17:31,170
you may lose your position as an editor.

340
00:17:31,170 --> 00:17:32,490
Got it.

341
00:17:32,490 --> 00:17:35,210
I'll isolate myself upstairs right away.

342
00:17:40,360 --> 00:17:48,769
[The Disappearing Mr Fox]

343
00:17:41,450 --> 00:17:42,769
[It's Valentine's Day.]

344
00:17:42,769 --> 00:17:44,450
[Instead of giving me a present,]

345
00:17:44,450 --> 00:17:46,529
[my boyfriend is running away
from me as I've caught a cold.]

346
00:17:46,529 --> 00:17:47,760
[What should I do?]

347
00:17:52,240 --> 00:18:01,700
[The Disappearing Mr Fox]

348
00:17:52,770 --> 00:17:55,410
[Maybe he's secretly
preparing a surprise.]

349
00:17:58,690 --> 00:18:01,690
More like a shock.

350
00:18:01,700 --> 00:18:05,130
[The Navy Hired by the Monkey]

351
00:18:02,370 --> 00:18:04,530
[More like a shock.]

352
00:18:06,570 --> 00:18:08,000
I don't get it.

353
00:18:08,290 --> 00:18:10,010
Why are girls obsessed

354
00:18:10,010 --> 00:18:11,850
about such boring festivals?

355
00:18:14,680 --> 00:18:15,910
[Selected Stories of Natsume Soseki]

356
00:18:18,680 --> 00:18:20,050
Guess I'll give her

357
00:18:20,050 --> 00:18:22,810
this original edition
as a Valentine's gift.

358
00:18:27,480 --> 00:18:30,830
[Stinky Monkey, after years of fighting,
you can have my favourite book. Mr Fox]

359
00:18:38,090 --> 00:18:39,730
What's going on?

360
00:18:40,970 --> 00:18:41,930
A blackout?

361
00:18:51,410 --> 00:18:51,890
Management.

362
00:18:51,890 --> 00:18:53,330
What's with the power cut?

363
00:18:54,050 --> 00:18:56,410
The circuit breaker tripped? Where is it?

364
00:18:57,400 --> 00:18:59,130
How would I know?

365
00:18:59,690 --> 00:19:01,480
Could you send someone here?

366
00:19:02,770 --> 00:19:04,610
Twenty minutes?

367
00:19:05,650 --> 00:19:07,090
Fine. Hurry up.

368
00:19:10,130 --> 00:19:11,850
The circuit breaker tripped. Stay still.

369
00:19:11,850 --> 00:19:13,480
Don't blame me if something happens.

370
00:19:13,800 --> 00:19:15,450
I'll be right back.

371
00:19:15,730 --> 00:19:17,330
Where are you going?

372
00:19:21,090 --> 00:19:22,810
Don't mind me. Stay where you are.

373
00:19:26,210 --> 00:19:27,880
He actually left

374
00:19:27,880 --> 00:19:29,410
his sick girlfriend alone

375
00:19:29,410 --> 00:19:31,080
in the dark house.

376
00:19:37,730 --> 00:19:39,450
Hi, I need cold medicine.

377
00:19:39,450 --> 00:19:41,850
The medicine we eat if we catch a cold.

378
00:19:41,850 --> 00:19:43,010
Okay.

379
00:19:44,210 --> 00:19:45,530
This one will do.

380
00:19:45,810 --> 00:19:46,810
Drink with warm water.

381
00:19:47,010 --> 00:19:48,090
You'll be fine with some warm water.

382
00:19:48,090 --> 00:19:49,170
I'll have this one.

383
00:19:49,170 --> 00:19:50,210
Okay.

384
00:19:57,160 --> 00:19:59,800
The power panel is right behind the porch.

385
00:19:59,800 --> 00:20:01,730
It can be fixed easily.

386
00:20:02,250 --> 00:20:04,770
Er Gou, why aren't you sleeping yet?

387
00:20:04,770 --> 00:20:07,770
Er Gou.

388
00:20:14,000 --> 00:20:17,690
Isn't this pyjamas my present to...

389
00:20:21,130 --> 00:20:24,390
[Stinky Monkey, after years of fighting,
you can have my favourite book. Mr Fox]

390
00:20:41,490 --> 00:20:43,450
The power is back on already?

391
00:20:45,410 --> 00:20:46,530
The circuit breaker tripped.

392
00:20:46,890 --> 00:20:48,000
But I fixed it.

393
00:20:50,050 --> 00:20:51,370
You're sick. Just stay in your room.

394
00:20:51,370 --> 00:20:52,730
Why come downstairs?

395
00:20:55,690 --> 00:20:56,930
Here.

396
00:20:57,330 --> 00:20:58,410
Take the medicine.

397
00:20:58,730 --> 00:20:59,760
Mr Zhou.

398
00:21:01,170 --> 00:21:03,330
I found something interesting.

399
00:21:14,690 --> 00:21:16,370
This pyjamas.

400
00:21:16,810 --> 00:21:19,930
It was Mr Fox's birthday gift from me.

401
00:21:24,250 --> 00:21:26,490
And the Natsume Soseki's book.

402
00:21:26,490 --> 00:21:29,530
Why is Mr Fox's signature here?

403
00:21:37,400 --> 00:21:39,810
Can you explain?

404
00:21:40,530 --> 00:21:42,770
What's going on?

405
00:21:49,770 --> 00:21:51,810
Why did you enter my study room again?

406
00:21:53,490 --> 00:21:56,130
Is that the only thing
you have to say to me?

407
00:22:19,970 --> 00:22:24,280
[The Navy Hired by the Monkey]

408
00:22:22,130 --> 00:22:24,280
[Where are you? I want the truth.]

409
00:22:31,630 --> 00:22:52,640
[The Disappearing Mr Fox]

410
00:22:33,290 --> 00:22:35,010
[In front of you.]

411
00:22:52,650 --> 00:22:55,400
When did you find out that I'm Monkey?

412
00:22:59,040 --> 00:23:01,770
A few days before
the Book of Luo He God's signing event.

413
00:23:03,410 --> 00:23:04,970
It was half a year ago.

414
00:23:04,970 --> 00:23:06,770
Why didn't you tell me?

415
00:23:07,250 --> 00:23:08,570
I didn't see the need,

416
00:23:08,570 --> 00:23:10,250
-so...
-You didn't see the need?

417
00:23:16,780 --> 00:23:18,800
[Added to Blocked list]

418
00:23:19,810 --> 00:23:21,370
You blocked me?

419
00:23:21,370 --> 00:23:22,370
Aren't you childish?

420
00:23:22,370 --> 00:23:23,800
You might as well block my real account.

421
00:23:26,530 --> 00:23:27,890
I don't want to talk to you.

422
00:23:27,890 --> 00:23:29,080
Where are you going?

423
00:23:29,520 --> 00:23:30,570
I have no idea.

424
00:23:30,570 --> 00:23:32,810
But I'm not talking to a liar now.

425
00:23:32,810 --> 00:23:35,450
Does it matter if I'm Mr Fox?

426
00:23:36,730 --> 00:23:38,210
Does it not?

427
00:23:38,760 --> 00:23:39,730
Don't you know

428
00:23:39,730 --> 00:23:41,050
I've always regarded Mr Fox

429
00:23:41,050 --> 00:23:42,210
as my best friend?

430
00:23:43,610 --> 00:23:44,920
You've been using this identity

431
00:23:44,920 --> 00:23:46,730
to spy on my life,

432
00:23:46,730 --> 00:23:49,250
thoughts and even feelings.

433
00:23:49,650 --> 00:23:51,520
What did you say when I asked

434
00:23:51,520 --> 00:23:52,770
if you're Mr Fox?

435
00:23:53,450 --> 00:23:54,490
Yes, I denied it.

436
00:23:54,490 --> 00:23:55,250
That's because I...

437
00:23:55,250 --> 00:23:57,090
Because you never wanted to tell me.

438
00:23:58,680 --> 00:23:59,730
It must be fun

439
00:23:59,730 --> 00:24:01,090
fooling me with two accounts.

440
00:24:01,090 --> 00:24:03,370
So you never planned to stop.

441
00:24:03,370 --> 00:24:04,890
Or maybe in your mind,

442
00:24:04,890 --> 00:24:06,720
an insignificant editor like me

443
00:24:06,720 --> 00:24:08,330
doesn't deserve to have
a popular writer like you

444
00:24:08,330 --> 00:24:09,610
to be my internet friend?

445
00:24:09,610 --> 00:24:10,850
Why must you

446
00:24:10,850 --> 00:24:12,530
make it so complicated? This...

447
00:24:12,530 --> 00:24:14,690
That should be my line.

448
00:24:14,690 --> 00:24:15,730
All this while,

449
00:24:15,730 --> 00:24:18,410
you can't stop making fun of me.

450
00:24:18,410 --> 00:24:19,570
Let me tell you.

451
00:24:19,570 --> 00:24:20,690
I won't continue

452
00:24:20,690 --> 00:24:21,810
such a childish game.

453
00:24:21,810 --> 00:24:23,050
Let's stop it here. Let's break up.

454
00:24:23,050 --> 00:24:24,810
Break up, you say?

455
00:24:25,170 --> 00:24:26,050
Who would put himself

456
00:24:26,050 --> 00:24:27,610
on the line for just a game?

457
00:24:27,610 --> 00:24:28,970
Put on the line?

458
00:24:29,290 --> 00:24:31,050
I'm the one who was kept in the dark.

459
00:24:31,050 --> 00:24:32,890
Yet you said you suffered the losses?

460
00:24:33,210 --> 00:24:34,930
Ridiculous.

461
00:24:35,210 --> 00:24:36,010
I do

462
00:24:36,320 --> 00:24:37,730
feel like I am a monkey

463
00:24:37,730 --> 00:24:39,050
being fooled now.

464
00:24:54,170 --> 00:24:55,450
He lied to me all this time.

465
00:24:55,450 --> 00:24:57,050
Am I a fool to him?

466
00:25:19,290 --> 00:25:20,570
Hello, Jiang Yu Cheng.

467
00:25:21,410 --> 00:25:23,570
You got it right again, jinx.

468
00:25:24,450 --> 00:25:26,090
This is bad.

469
00:25:46,130 --> 00:25:47,730
Er Gou.

470
00:25:47,730 --> 00:25:48,690
After I'm out of here,

471
00:25:48,690 --> 00:25:50,570
don't forget to eat.

472
00:25:50,570 --> 00:25:52,730
Don't be like someone.

473
00:26:24,530 --> 00:26:26,610
She went to work already?

474
00:26:27,650 --> 00:26:29,760
She's trying to avoid me again.

475
00:26:38,730 --> 00:26:39,570
Chu Li.

476
00:26:39,810 --> 00:26:41,050
Why are you spacing out?

477
00:26:41,730 --> 00:26:42,770
Ah Xiang.

478
00:26:42,770 --> 00:26:43,810
Can I

479
00:26:43,810 --> 00:26:45,850
stay at your place for a day or two?

480
00:26:45,850 --> 00:26:46,370
What happened?

481
00:26:46,370 --> 00:26:48,330
Did your new landlord kick you out?

482
00:26:48,330 --> 00:26:49,450
That's not the case.

483
00:26:49,680 --> 00:26:50,690
The Disappearing Amusement Park

484
00:26:50,690 --> 00:26:52,850
is going to launch earlier, isn't it?

485
00:26:52,850 --> 00:26:55,130
My workload suddenly becomes heavier.

486
00:26:55,130 --> 00:26:57,850
Your house is near the printing factory.

487
00:26:57,850 --> 00:27:00,680
So, it's more convenient.

488
00:27:00,680 --> 00:27:01,450
Sure.

489
00:27:01,450 --> 00:27:03,490
Just move in.

490
00:27:04,610 --> 00:27:05,570
Really?

491
00:27:06,810 --> 00:27:08,650
I'm ready.

492
00:27:10,690 --> 00:27:12,330
No problem.

493
00:27:12,930 --> 00:27:14,320
Thank you.

494
00:27:16,010 --> 00:27:17,810
You called me in the middle of the night

495
00:27:17,810 --> 00:27:18,770
just because

496
00:27:18,770 --> 00:27:20,730
she found out you're Mr Fox

497
00:27:20,730 --> 00:27:22,530
and you don't know what to do about it?

498
00:27:22,530 --> 00:27:23,970
Don't gloat over that.

499
00:27:23,970 --> 00:27:24,810
You still

500
00:27:24,810 --> 00:27:25,880
don't stand a chance.

501
00:27:25,880 --> 00:27:27,770
I'm already over her.

502
00:27:28,250 --> 00:27:29,890
I regard her as my sister now.

503
00:27:29,890 --> 00:27:31,160
If I were her,

504
00:27:31,160 --> 00:27:33,330
given how my boyfriend

505
00:27:33,330 --> 00:27:35,330
neglected our first Valentine's Day,

506
00:27:35,330 --> 00:27:37,370
and lied to me,

507
00:27:38,450 --> 00:27:39,770
I would certainly

508
00:27:39,770 --> 00:27:40,930
break up with you.

509
00:27:40,930 --> 00:27:41,810
Shut up.

510
00:27:41,810 --> 00:27:43,330
Now that makes me furious.

511
00:27:43,330 --> 00:27:45,850
How could she say "break up" so easily?

512
00:27:45,850 --> 00:27:46,970
Who am I to her?

513
00:27:46,970 --> 00:27:48,410
Are you sure you want me to shut up?

514
00:27:48,410 --> 00:27:49,890
Fine. I thought you asked me out

515
00:27:49,890 --> 00:27:51,400
to give you advice.

516
00:27:52,410 --> 00:27:53,450
Say it already.

517
00:27:55,970 --> 00:27:57,770
Firstly, you must apologise.

518
00:27:57,890 --> 00:27:58,770
Then,

519
00:27:58,930 --> 00:28:00,050
be it she's angry about

520
00:28:00,050 --> 00:28:01,290
you denying to be Mr Fox,

521
00:28:01,290 --> 00:28:02,960
or not preparing for Valentine's Day,

522
00:28:02,960 --> 00:28:04,490
when she said she wants a break up,

523
00:28:04,490 --> 00:28:06,800
that means she feels insecure.

524
00:28:06,800 --> 00:28:07,650
Simply put,

525
00:28:07,650 --> 00:28:09,610
she is unconfident

526
00:28:09,610 --> 00:28:10,650
about your relationship.

527
00:28:10,650 --> 00:28:12,130
Unconfident?

528
00:28:12,930 --> 00:28:15,130
I never said no to her.

529
00:28:15,160 --> 00:28:17,170
I even did things I wouldn't do

530
00:28:17,170 --> 00:28:18,360
in the past.

531
00:28:18,890 --> 00:28:20,120
Men and women

532
00:28:20,120 --> 00:28:21,440
are totally different.

533
00:28:21,440 --> 00:28:22,410
Sometimes, we think

534
00:28:22,410 --> 00:28:23,770
that we've done everything,

535
00:28:23,770 --> 00:28:25,210
and that living harmoniously together

536
00:28:25,210 --> 00:28:26,280
is the promise we gave.

537
00:28:26,280 --> 00:28:27,890
But diamond rings, flowers,

538
00:28:27,890 --> 00:28:30,250
and being romantically ceremonious

539
00:28:30,250 --> 00:28:32,250
mean more to girls.

540
00:28:32,250 --> 00:28:33,000
It

541
00:28:33,000 --> 00:28:34,690
might be a white lie to you.

542
00:28:34,970 --> 00:28:36,050
But to her,

543
00:28:36,050 --> 00:28:37,730
if you would lie on a small matter,

544
00:28:37,730 --> 00:28:39,810
then you might also
lie about important things.

545
00:28:39,810 --> 00:28:42,330
She may think that you've never wanted
to spend the rest of your life with her.

546
00:28:42,330 --> 00:28:44,440
That's not right.

547
00:28:44,760 --> 00:28:46,290
She's my chosen one.

548
00:28:46,290 --> 00:28:48,250
Had you told Chu Li earlier,

549
00:28:48,250 --> 00:28:49,490
things would have been fine.

550
00:28:54,490 --> 00:28:56,130
What should I do now?

551
00:28:58,330 --> 00:28:59,730
It's easy

552
00:28:59,730 --> 00:29:00,720
to ask for her forgiveness.

553
00:29:03,920 --> 00:29:05,210
When you see her next time,

554
00:29:05,240 --> 00:29:06,610
apologise first.

555
00:29:07,000 --> 00:29:08,640
Then, hold her in your arms.

556
00:29:11,530 --> 00:29:12,930
And kiss her.

557
00:29:12,930 --> 00:29:14,410
Then say it out loud

558
00:29:14,410 --> 00:29:15,570
that you like her,

559
00:29:15,570 --> 00:29:16,490
you love her,

560
00:29:16,490 --> 00:29:18,330
and that she's fated to be yours.

561
00:29:22,130 --> 00:29:24,570
Is such pretension and
exaggeration necessary?

562
00:29:27,450 --> 00:29:29,570
Prepare to get dumped then.

563
00:29:29,570 --> 00:29:30,570
Not really.

564
00:29:30,570 --> 00:29:32,050
Maybe to Chu Li,

565
00:29:32,050 --> 00:29:33,810
she's not dumping you.

